Within 5 days after a petition for adoption of a child is filed under this Part III of this subtitle with a juvenile court, the clerk shall send a copy of the petition, with the notice of filing that was attached to the petition, to:
the local department with custody of the child;
each of the child's living parents who has not waived the right to notice;
each living parent's last attorney of record in the CINA case; and
the child's last attorney of record in the CINA case.
